fields.value: Family conflict unit (CAPS-FAMCON and CAPS-FAMQQ modules)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Questions pertain to parental conflict, such as whether the parents ever separated or divorced, and the ways in which families resolve conflicts. Questions about arguments and physical fighting are also asked to provide some information about the level of severity of conflict in the home.

Questions asked of all respondents, irrespective of family status were how close they feel to each parent and to their favorite sibling, parental support, parental expectations, family methods of handl ing disagreements, family rules, family values and respondent's agreement with parents on these, contact with parents during academic year, family decision-making, physical abuse, admiration for family members, family togetherness.

Also included are the respondent's overall evaluation of his/her parent's marriage and the ways in which the respondent feels that his/her parent's marriage has influenced his/her own dating/marriage relationships.

Questions asked only of respondents whose parents are 'married to each other' were how much of their free time the respondent's parents spend together, who the parents rely on when they have problems, what they disagree about.

Questions administered to respondents w ho indicated that their parent was a widow or widower. asked which of the respondent's parents is deceased, how old the R was when the parent died, who R has lived with since the parent's death.

Questions administered to respondents who indicated that their parents were separated or divorced asked how old the respondent was when the parents separated, how many separations there have been, respondent's residence since the separation/divorce, contact with the non-custodial parent, conflict between the parents before and after the separation/divorce, dating relationships of the parents and physical abuse.

Questions administered to respondents who indicated that at least one pa rent had remarried concerned conflicts in the parents' remarriages, relationships with step/half siblings (if any). These questions were asked of Rs with divorced or widowed parents.

In CAPS/85 these questions were administered in two units: FAMCON and FAMQQ.

No standard scoring.
